1
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:02,710
Koharu.

2
00:00:03,370 --> 00:00:05,840
I'll turn on the monitor.

3
00:00:07,705 --> 00:00:10,250
- Koharu.
- Move over.

4
00:00:10,250 --> 00:00:11,040
Sorry.

5
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:13,925
Koharu, can you hear me? Koharu?

6
00:00:13,925 --> 00:00:14,970
- Oxygen, 5 liters.
- Yes.

7
00:00:14,970 --> 00:00:16,340
Koharu?

8
00:00:21,090 --> 00:00:22,390
How's Koharu?

9
00:00:23,715 --> 00:00:27,940
Seems like a temporary seizure.
She's okay now.

10
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:30,640
Thank goodness.

11
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:36,690
Really, I'm so glad...

12
00:00:46,940 --> 00:00:49,100
Are you okay?

13
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:52,800
I wonder...

14
00:00:54,690 --> 00:00:57,040
how many more times I'll worry.

15
00:00:59,380 --> 00:01:00,560
I see.

16
00:01:01,220 --> 00:01:02,230
Yeah.

17
00:01:04,860 --> 00:01:06,170
That's upsetting.

18
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:09,780
<i>Luckily, she's okay now.</i>

19
00:01:10,525 --> 00:01:12,322
<i>Yeah.</i>

20
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:16,827
<i>Why today of all days?
We got the best seats, you know?</i>

21
00:01:18,900 --> 00:01:19,940
Hey...

22
00:01:21,140 --> 00:01:23,670
I want to ask you for a favor.

23
00:02:11,210 --> 00:02:15,960
[The Final Episode]

24
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:18,580
Koharu.

25
00:02:24,610 --> 00:02:26,210
Kakeru?

26
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:29,860
What about the fireworks?

27
00:02:36,510 --> 00:02:38,300
What time is it now?

28
00:02:39,820 --> 00:02:41,330
It's night now.

29
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:46,670
They said you need to rest for a while.

30
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:50,920
I see.

31
00:02:56,170 --> 00:02:58,000
Was it all for nothing?

32
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:05,230
But I tried so hard.

33
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:12,460
And you all were helping me this whole time.

34
00:03:14,895 --> 00:03:16,430
It's okay.

35
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:17,830
What's okay?

36
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:22,050
We didn't make it in the end.

37
00:03:26,070 --> 00:03:28,840
After all that work to get here...

38
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:37,490
We did make it.

39
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:40,960
Huh?

40
00:03:49,290 --> 00:03:51,760
Give me your hand.

41
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:09,690
Are you ready?

42
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,360
Boom.

43
00:04:35,370 --> 00:04:36,800
Fireworks?

44
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,290
What is this?

45
00:04:47,950 --> 00:04:48,980
Right now...

46
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:57,410
the fireworks at the venue
are filling the entire wall.

47
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:05,040
We couldn't go to the venue.

48
00:05:08,610 --> 00:05:11,170
But the same view is right here...

49
00:05:12,590 --> 00:05:14,650
spread out before your eyes.

50
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:35,907
<i>Koharu!</i>

51
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:39,040
Yuuko?

52
00:05:39,805 --> 00:05:43,440
Ushio and Yuuko helped me set it up.

53
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:46,060
<i>I'm so glad you're awake!</i>

54
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:51,270
<i>Hey! Coming to you live from the best seats!</i>

55
00:05:51,270 --> 00:05:53,655
Ushio, keep your voice down.

56
00:05:53,655 --> 00:05:55,295
<i>Why should I?</i>

57
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:10,860
Thank you, everyone...

58
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,360
Kakeru,

59
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,530
do you remember?

60
00:07:04,930 --> 00:07:06,030
What?

61
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:10,620
The reason why I love fireworks.

62
00:07:15,932 --> 00:07:17,513
No matter who you are...

63
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:21,990
the moment the fireworks shoot up...

64
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,230
everyone looks up.

65
00:07:28,450 --> 00:07:30,230
That's why you like them.

66
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,410
Yeah.

67
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:38,370
But that's not the only reason.

68
00:07:43,156 --> 00:07:46,946
Have you ever read a book
called The Diary of a Young Girl?

69
00:07:48,410 --> 00:07:49,420
No.

70
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:55,070
It's the diary of a girl in harsh times,

71
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:59,020
never knowing if she'd be alive the next day.

72
00:08:01,870 --> 00:08:03,940
My wish is...

73
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:10,550
to go on living even after my death.

74
00:08:15,698 --> 00:08:18,957
I wish I could live in a way that leaves

75
00:08:18,957 --> 00:08:23,046
a mark on someone's heart,
like fireworks do.

76
00:08:24,010 --> 00:08:26,450
I've always thought that.

77
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:33,750
I think...

78
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:37,370
And I'll only say this once...

79
00:08:38,855 --> 00:08:39,870
Huh?

80
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:45,980
Koharu.

81
00:08:47,930 --> 00:08:51,060
You've burned yourself deeply into my heart.

82
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:57,430
Why only say it once?

83
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:08,650
Please...

84
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:14,890
let me stay by your side.

85
00:09:22,370 --> 00:09:23,440
I will.

86
00:09:38,330 --> 00:09:44,740
[9 Years Later]

87
00:10:00,190 --> 00:10:01,900
Thank you.

88
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:06,390
Hey, over here!

89
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:09,250
Excuse me, one more beer please.

90
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:10,890
Okay, another beer.

91
00:10:10,890 --> 00:10:12,670
- Hello.
- Welcome.

92
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:14,780
Sorry for the wait.

93
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:16,825
It's okay. We started anyway.

94
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:19,070
- Beer's fine, right?
- Yeah.

95
00:10:19,805 --> 00:10:22,682
Long day, huh? Is everything okay at home?

96
00:10:22,682 --> 00:10:25,550
- My mother-in-law's got it.
- I see.

97
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:27,835
Your limit's two drinks.

98
00:10:27,835 --> 00:10:29,115
Yeah.

99
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:35,369
Excuse me. Your beer.

100
00:10:35,369 --> 00:10:36,869
Thank you.

101
00:10:38,870 --> 00:10:40,090
Well then.

102
00:10:47,310 --> 00:10:48,720
Let's stay cheerful.

103
00:10:49,745 --> 00:10:51,580
Okay.

104
00:10:51,580 --> 00:10:53,105
Long time no see!

105
00:10:53,105 --> 00:10:54,675
Cheers!

106
00:11:05,365 --> 00:11:07,670
You're practically an old man now!

107
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:08,915
So what? It's fine.

108
00:11:08,915 --> 00:11:10,785
We're in our late twenties.

109
00:11:13,035 --> 00:11:16,260
Thanks for coming today.

110
00:11:16,260 --> 00:11:18,290
Of course we'd come.

111
00:11:18,290 --> 00:11:22,480
I've been to the second, sixth,
and every memorial after.

112
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:25,090
He was really bummed
he couldn't make it last year.

113
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:27,570
Working at a trading company sucks.

114
00:11:27,570 --> 00:11:29,905
Why do I gotta work in the sticks abroad?

115
00:11:29,905 --> 00:11:31,355
Hmm.

116
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:35,660
Ah, your signature aloofness.
Takes me back.

117
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:40,100
This bar takes me back, too.

118
00:11:42,938 --> 00:11:46,233
We could've picked a nicer place at our age.

119
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:47,783
But it was here.

120
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:52,160
Where we all first met.

121
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,400
Yeah.

122
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:00,700
And also...

123
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,740
Hey, that's...

124
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:13,290
Things will get better.

125
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:17,760
You even got permission to go out today.

126
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:22,616
The other hospital can get you
the latest treatments, right?

127
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:23,616
Yeah.

128
00:12:25,660 --> 00:12:27,960
I won't lose.

129
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,720
Yeah.

130
00:12:34,610 --> 00:12:36,290
Oh, right.

131
00:12:42,110 --> 00:12:43,350
Here.

132
00:12:47,670 --> 00:12:49,150
What is this?

133
00:12:51,410 --> 00:12:56,053
How about we make a new one with this?

134
00:12:57,490 --> 00:12:58,490
Huh?

135
00:13:00,530 --> 00:13:02,830
A list of things you want to do.

136
00:13:03,590 --> 00:13:05,050
Part 2.

137
00:13:14,610 --> 00:13:16,090
Go to the sea.

138
00:13:18,350 --> 00:13:20,630
Soak in a mountain hot spring.

139
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:25,290
What else?

140
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:27,500
Anything?

141
00:13:31,690 --> 00:13:33,280
There are so many.

142
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:39,420
First, beat this illness.

143
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:44,410
Graduate from college properly.

144
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:48,350
I'd like to try working, too.

145
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,020
And then...

146
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:55,490
get married, maybe.

147
00:13:58,126 --> 00:14:02,096
Maybe even build a family someday.

148
00:14:15,330 --> 00:14:16,750
Kakeru?

149
00:14:17,630 --> 00:14:20,180
No, it's nothing.

150
00:14:41,530 --> 00:14:44,050
I'm glad I met you, Kakeru.

151
00:14:53,330 --> 00:14:54,410
Me too.

152
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,470
I'm so glad I met you, Koharu.

153
00:15:17,230 --> 00:15:20,990
"Gather with everyone again at that bar."

154
00:15:23,655 --> 00:15:25,510
And with this,

155
00:15:25,510 --> 00:15:27,295
it's complete.

156
00:15:27,295 --> 00:15:28,625
Wow.

157
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:31,520
So that's why.

158
00:15:32,540 --> 00:15:35,440
I thought it would be the easiest,

159
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,495
but it ended up being the last.

160
00:15:37,495 --> 00:15:39,065
That's my fault.

161
00:15:39,805 --> 00:15:45,350
Koharu came back to Tokyo
just as I got sent overseas.

162
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:46,465
That's right.

163
00:15:46,465 --> 00:15:48,535
Back me up here!

164
00:15:54,590 --> 00:15:55,630
Kakeru?

165
00:15:59,910 --> 00:16:01,870
We've come a long way, huh?

166
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:04,730
Yeah, we have.

167
00:16:06,235 --> 00:16:08,770
You worked hard. Really hard.

168
00:16:10,130 --> 00:16:13,670
Both you and Koharu.

169
00:16:17,090 --> 00:16:18,090
Yeah.

170
00:16:23,230 --> 00:16:24,540
Kakeru.

171
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,560
What's next for you?

172
00:17:22,305 --> 00:17:24,810
Welcome back.

173
00:17:24,810 --> 00:17:27,500
I'm sorry for
making you do everything at home.

174
00:17:44,263 --> 00:17:45,383
Everything...

175
00:17:46,220 --> 00:17:47,710
is done now.

176
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:52,390
It's all over now.

177
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,650
From now on...

178
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:03,380
not being able to make new memories
with Koharu is...

179
00:18:06,910 --> 00:18:09,130
She gave me something.

180
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:13,680
To pass along to you...

181
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,460
when you finish the list.

182
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:55,500
<i>Kakeru.</i>

183
00:18:57,860 --> 00:18:59,460
<i>Um...</i>

184
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:05,704
<i>If you're listening to this,</i>

185
00:19:05,704 --> 00:19:09,384
<i>that means you all managed
to gather at that bar.</i>

186
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:12,210
<i>How was it?</i>

187
00:19:14,180 --> 00:19:18,000
<i>I bet Yuuko and Ushio talked non-stop,</i>

188
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:21,100
<i>and you just went, "Hm,"</i>

189
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:24,280
<i>acting all aloof, right?</i>

190
00:19:33,420 --> 00:19:34,890
<i>Are you doing well?</i>

191
00:19:38,020 --> 00:19:40,620
<i>Now that the bucket list is all done,</i>

192
00:19:41,530 --> 00:19:46,420
<i>Kakeru, are you wondering what to do next?</i>

193
00:19:48,138 --> 00:19:52,080
<i>That really worries me.</i>

194
00:19:56,540 --> 00:19:59,560
<i>In the winter of my freshman year,</i>

195
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,420
<i>normally, at that time,</i>

196
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:04,790
<i>my life would have ended.</i>

197
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:11,640
<i>But, because you were there...</i>

198
00:20:14,930 --> 00:20:17,130
<i>I was able to live this long.</i>

199
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:22,380
<i>Because of those fireworks,</i>

200
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:25,310
<i>I could look up countless times for strength.</i>

201
00:20:26,450 --> 00:20:28,710
<i>I was able to fulfill so many dreams.</i>

202
00:20:31,335 --> 00:20:36,060
<i>Every single day was so, so fun,
I couldn't help myself.</i>

203
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:48,230
<i>Those were really...</i>

204
00:20:54,330 --> 00:20:56,660
<i>happy times for me.</i>

205
00:21:03,660 --> 00:21:04,850
<i>So...</i>

206
00:21:05,780 --> 00:21:08,540
<i>From now on, I want you too,</i>

207
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:12,690
<i>to look up and live.</i>

208
00:21:14,065 --> 00:21:18,940
<i>When things get hard,
remember the fireworks we saw together.</i>

209
00:21:20,460 --> 00:21:23,880
<i>I know you can do it, Kakeru.</i>

210
00:21:27,390 --> 00:21:30,420
<i>Most importantly...
I've told you this, right?</i>

211
00:21:32,830 --> 00:21:37,800
<i>Losing something doesn't mean
you lose everything.</i>

212
00:21:41,060 --> 00:21:43,330
<i>Precious things still remain.</i>

213
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:50,300
<i>Please, together with those treasures...</i>

214
00:21:52,780 --> 00:21:54,920
<i>for my sake too...</i>

215
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:59,210
<i>live your life with a smile.</i>

216
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:03,930
<i>One last thing.</i>

217
00:22:06,447 --> 00:22:07,787
<i>Kakeru.</i>

218
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,760
<i>I'll always love you.</i>

219
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:45,450
Thank you.

220
00:22:57,765 --> 00:23:00,900
Daddy, when are we going?

221
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:02,345
I'm coming now.

222
00:23:02,345 --> 00:23:04,285
Let's go!

223
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:19,274
<i>This is a story
about my unseen love with you,</i>

224
00:23:19,274 --> 00:23:21,544
<i>who ran beneath the clear sky.</i>

225
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,050
<i>And...</i>

226
00:23:27,060 --> 00:23:29,690
<i>that story will continue forever.</i>

227
00:23:31,950 --> 00:23:33,710
I'll be going now.

228
00:23:36,675 --> 00:23:38,030
Sorry to keep you waiting.

229
00:23:38,030 --> 00:23:39,945
- So slow.
- Let's go.
